data.title: Bonerama Confirm 25th Anniversary Show Details
data.meta_description: The definitive resource for jambands (jam bands) and their fans, established in 1998. Daily news, features, set lists, reviews, charts, columns, audio, video, merchandise and more. Affiliated with the Relix Media Group LLC.
data.text:
Erica Falls, Papa Mali, Arsene DeLay, BariRama and Mike Lemmler will all join Bonerama during their 25th anniversary show tomorrow. The guest-heavy celebration will take place at New Orleans’ Tipitina’s. It will be the group’s first appearance at Tip’s in a number of years.

Mark Mullins and Craig Klein formed the popular New Orlans brass band in 1998 while they were members of Harry Connick Jr.’s band. BariRama’s features Jason Mingledorff, Dan Oestreicher and Alonzo Bowens all on bari saxophone.
